[0.000, "o", "                               \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128magentmake engine from a single `goal.md`. Stretch goal reached: **the compiler                                         \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mcompiles itself, byte-exact fixed point (gen1 output == gen2)**.                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m```                                                                                                                    \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mgoal.md ──▶ classify (prd tier) ──▶ plan (7 components) ──▶ build agents ──▶ review: PASS                              \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m```                       "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                             \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m## The prompt trick: staged bootstrap encoded in the PRD                                                               \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mThe interesting part is not the code — it's how `goal.md` is written so that                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mLLM build agents can pull off a compiler bootstrap without a human in the loop:                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;"]
[0.000, "o", "2;128;128;128m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m1. **Stages as components.** The PRD hard-splits the impossible ask (\"Forth                                            \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   compiler in Forth\") into three stages with a dependency arrow: stage0 =                                             \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   seed interpreter (Python), stage1 = compiler *in Forth run by stage0*,                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   stage2 = equivalence gate. Each stage is independently checkable, so the                                            \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   engine's DAG scheduling does the bootstrap ordering for free.                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b"]
[0.000, "o", "[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m2. **The interface is the spec.** The PRD pins the exact compiler-support words                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   (`token`, `h.`, `h=`, `h>n`, `s\"` — string *handles* on an integer stack)                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   that stage0 must provide and stage1 may consume. Two different agents built                                         \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   the two sides without talking to each other; the pinned word contract is the                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   only channel.                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m3. **Goldens pinned in the PRD, not generated.** Test programs AND their exact       "]
[0.000, "o", "                                  \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   output bytes (down to `.`'s trailing space) are written into `goal.md`, with                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   an explicit \"do not regenerate goldens from program output\" clause. Agents                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   can't game the gate; interpreted == compiled == pinned-bytes is the proof.                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m4. **Stretch isolated + honesty clause.** Self-hosting lives in its own                                                \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   component whose `check.sh` must exit 0 *either way* and write the honest                                            \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   outcome to `RESULT.md` (\"Do not fake it.\"). "]
[0.000, "o", "Failure can't wedge the build,                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m   and success can't be bluffed — the reviewer re-runs the chain.                                                      \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m## Result                                                                                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m- **First run, zero retry loops.** All 7 components green, review `VERDICT: PASS`,                                     \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m  `wfch"]
[0.000, "o", "eck: PASS 32/32 (score 1)`.                                                                                     \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m- Stage0: ~190-line stdlib Python Forth (nested `if/else/then`, `begin/until`,                                         \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m  `do/loop/i`, variables, both comment styles, string-handle words).                                                   \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m- Stage1: `src/stage1/compiler.fs` — zero Python, run by stage0, emits                                                 \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m  standalone Python with embedded runtime. fib/fizzbuzz/stackops compile to                                            \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m  byte-exact golden matches.                                                                                           \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[4"]
[0.000, "o", "8;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m- Selfhost: `src/selfhost/compiler.fs` (stage1 extended so its emitted runtime                                         \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m  also carries the string table + `token`) compiles itself; the self-compiled                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m  compiler compiles fib to a golden match, and gen1 == gen2 byte-identical.                                            \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m  Honest deviations recorded in `src/selfhost/RESULT.md` (e.g. multi-word                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m  `.\" ...\"` strings can't survive whitespace tokenization — the PRD's `token`                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m  is deliberately minimal).                                                                             "]
[0.000, "o", "               \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m## Run it                                                                                                              \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m```sh                                                                                                                  \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mmake            # full pipeline (needs pi CLI); resumes wherever it stopped                                            \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mmake progress   # census                                          "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                     \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mbash src/gate/check.sh        # stage-2 equivalence gate                                                               \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mbash src/selfhost/check.sh    # self-hosting chain                                                                     \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m../../evals/wfcheck .         # workflow-correctness score                                                             \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m```                                                                                                                    \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mArtifacts: `buildlog.txt` (f"]
[0.000, "o", "ull engine run), `shots/` (progress, gate,                                                 \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mselfhost fixed point, dep graph), `REVIEW.md` + `build/report.md` (reviewer),                                          \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m`build/wfscore.json`.                                                                                                  \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128m                                                                                                                       \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m \u001b[38;2;128;128;128mstack <0>:\u001b[39m                                                                                                             \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;40;50;40m                                                                                                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b]133;A\u0007\u001b[48;2;52;53;65"]
[0.000, "o", "m                                                                                                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;52;53;65m \u001b[38;2;138;190;183m2. \u001b[39m\u001b[38;2;212;212;212mWrite the program to src/tests/sierpinski.fs using: s\" \u001b[39m\u001b[38;2;212;212;212m<program text>\u001b[39m\u001b[38;2;212;212;212m\" s\" src/tests/sierpinski.fs\" fwrite. HARD     \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;52;53;65m    \u001b[38;2;212;212;212mconstraint: an s\" payload cannot contain a double-quote character, so the program file must not use .\" strings —    \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[48;2;52;53;65m    \u001b[38;2;212;212;212mnumbers, emit, loops only. s\" payloads may span multiple lines.\u001b[39m                                                     \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b]133;B\u0007\u001b]133;C\u0007\u001b[48;2;52;53;65m                                                                                                                        \u001b[49m\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K \u001b[38;2;102;102;102mSteering: 3. Prove it: s\" src/tests/sierpinski.fs\" load must"]
