[0.042, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[12A\r\u001b[2K\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K \u001b[3m\u001b[38;2;128;128;128mI need to refactor the parity test to use a begin/until loop instead of the current 16-iteration do/loop, checking     \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K \u001b[3;38;2;128;128;128mthat each digit of c is less than or equal to the corresponding digit of r. I'm defining a word that compares the      \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K \u001b[3;38;2;128;128;128mdigits by repeatedly checking if c mod 2 exceeds r mod 2, and if so, fails the test, otherwise continuing the loop     \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K \u001b[3;38;2;128;128;128muntil both values are exhausted.\u001b[39m\u001b[23m                                                                                       \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K Rewriting the parity word to use the digit-comparison rule directly with a \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mbegin/until\u001b[39m loop (replacing the 16-pass     \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K \u001b[38;2;138;190;183mdo/loop\u001b[39m AND emulation):                                                                                                \u001b[0m\u001b]8;;\u0007\r\r\n\u001b[2K\u001b[0m\u001b]"]
